INFLUENZA PANDEMIC, 1918 (03)
=============================
Date: Mon, 24 Mar 1997 14:32:27 -0600
To: promed@usa.healthnet.org
From: scherba@staff.uiuc.edu (scherba)
Subject: Re: PRO/AH> Influenza pandemic, 1918 (02)
3/24/97
To my knowledge, the classic swine influenza was not clinically reported in
the U.S. until the 1918 pandemic. Does anyone know if there is an earlier
report of swine influenza? If this is true, can it truly be determined if
the influenza virus was zoonotic from or to pigs?
